HEADWORD: H-bomb
<hw>H"-bomb`</hw> <pr>(⟦amac⟧ch"b⟦ocr⟧mb`)</pr> <pos>n.</pos> <def>The
<altname>hydrogen bomb</altname>, a thermonuclear weapon that releases
atomic energy by union of hydrogen nuclei at high temperatures to form
helium. The force of its explosion may range from one to hundreds of
megatons of TNT equivalent.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> hydrogen bomb, fusion bomb, thermonuclear
bomb.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

